<br>
Then...<br>
<br>
Through dried, cracked lips words begin to come forth, soft and low at first and the sounds of a symphony softly playing could be heard on the winds blowing around her. Her captor leaned her scally head down and tried to hear what the crazed Half-Elf was saying.<br>
<br>
~ When I'm alone ~<br>
<br>
~ I dream of the horizon ~<br>
<br>
~ and words fail me ~<br>
<br>
~ there is no light ~<br>
<br>
~ in a room where there is no sun ~<br>
<br>
~ and there is no sun if you are not here with me...with me ~<br>
<br>
~ from every window unfurl my heart ~<br>
<br>
~ the heart that you have one ~<br>
<br>
~ into me you've poured the light ~<br>
<br>
~ the light that you have found by the side of the road ~<br>
<br>
Steadily as the wind grew less and less violent, so did the Maidens song grow stronger and louder with the symphony of music also building higher and higher. The giant scaley head of the Half-elfs captor was so enthralled by the defiant song that SHE the icy bitch failed to notice a small speck climbing down from the giant ridge up above them and down into the icy bowl valley. We see a human garbed in modest clothing climbing down the icy slope with his bare hands. To get hand holds in the ice the human man slams his fist into pure ice and makes a hand hold. his eyes see the scene below him and his eyes do narrow, and he triples his efforts to reach the bottom practially sliding halfway down the side of the ice bowl, then catching himself ripping his fingers as he does this, but he notices the pain..NOT...he keeps his eyes trained upon the half-elf maiden and his iron will is driving him onward all the while his mithril heart pumping his life force to continue on and not...FAIL...just then a song reaches the human males ears and he suddlent gasps and looks down at the scene below...<br>
<br>
~ Time to say Goodbye ~<br>
<br>
~ places that ive never seen or experienced with you ~<br>
<br>
~ now I shall ~<br>
<br>
~ Ill sail with you ~<br>
<br>
~ upon ships across the sea ~<br>
<br>
~ seas that exist no more ~ <br>
<br>
~ Time to say...........Goodbye ~<br>
<br>
<br>
with the last verse the winds have completely stopped and the cresendo of the symphony has reached its peak. a great sound of music wich dissapears as quickly as it came...and in one last act of defiance the Half-elf maiden cracks her swollen eyes open one last time to sea the light...the light that he gave her. Then the Maiden slumps down hanging from her straps lifeless.<br>
<br>
nnNNNNnOOooooOOO !!!!!<br>
<br>
...Upon seeing this the human man leaps the rest of the distance down some 500 feet and lands on top of VOX's head and with a wrath unseen in a mortal man...he pummeled this scaley beasts head with a fury of the sun God and with anger given to him from the God of battle. Vox who was already mezzed by the singing of her captive was caught unaware and was now being thrashed upon as if the Gods herself were throwing boulders down from the heavens...Vox was able to throw the human man aside and not wanting to tempt his rage again she takes to the air and flies off to find easier prey....<br>
<br>
...The human man quickly rushes to the fallen maiden and easily breaks her bods with his magnaficient strength. He holds her gently in his muscle laden arms and cradles her lifeless body. There is no breath from her lips and her heart has no rythmitic beat, and so he beigins to weep...He curses the Gods for not allowing him to get her quicker and for not taking his worthless life, a life that he has squandered in the pursuit of personal gains and frivalitary things. He prays to Gods to granthim one wish...that if there is still hope for him, then please take from him the strength needed to revive this Maiden and he will begin his life as if he were born anew...the wind stirs and it begins to snow..a soft gentle snow..and a snow flake falls upon her lips and the young man does gently kiss her cracked lips and almost without warning...warmth and light erupt from the lifeless body..and no more does a broken Half-elf maiden lay in his arms but a 12 foot tall human female wreathed in loving flames and smelling of roses...the Goddess of Love has answerd your prayer and I shall hold you to it...Master Pren !!...I command you to watch over this, young Maiden for in saving her life you have altered the events of her life. So I bid thee good luck Master Pren...you were a true hero today and we in the heavens are proud to know that there is still hope in man and this world...<br>
<br>
...The Goddess dost dissapear in a shining blast of white light and in her place lays the Half-elf maiden now made whole and laying on the snow...her Raven locks fall in front of her diamond like eyes and her milky white skin is fresh and soft like a babys skin..she stands pulling her robes tighter around her...then she sees the heroic figure standing in fron of her and she cracks a smile and says...&quot;who are you?<br>
<br>
<br>
&quot;This is the real question, Who are you Pren?&quot;  <br>
